one can meditate upon\n&gt;&gt; the light of the Sun. This is why =\r\nthis meaning for the Gayatri mantra is\n&gt;&gt; always taken first.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; vareNya=\r\nm =3D whatever we can ask / desire. Through all karmas and\n&gt;&gt; upaasanaas, w=\r\nhatever fruits we may ask for is vareNyam. =93Savitaa&quot; is the\n&gt;&gt; fruit of a=\r\nll karmas ... this is taught in the Chandogya Upanishad. [ A long\n&gt;&gt; explan=\r\nation follows, which is omitted here ].  We meditate upon the\n&gt;&gt; splendor o=\r\nf the sun, which is vareNyam.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; We meditate upon that Savitaa (yaH) who=\r\n impels (prachodayaat) our (naH)\n&gt;&gt; thoughts (dhiyaH). He blesses us with s=\r\nubtle eyesight. Without his light,\n&gt;&gt; we would not be able to distinguish d=\r\nifferent objects. This is explained in\n&gt;&gt; the Aitaterya Upanishad =93The su=\r\nn, having become eyesight, entered the\n&gt;&gt; eyes=94. He thus blesses all livi=\r\nng beings.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; ----\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; Sent from Windows Mail\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt; \n&gt;\n\r\n--bcaec554d60eddcbbc04d357b677\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=windows-1252\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;Dear Hari,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;=A0&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Thanks for the nice story.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv&gt;=A0&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;=A0&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&gt;&gt; It usually takes me 15 minutes to co=\r\nmplete 28 times recital silently and without lip movement. By this timing, =\r\nI really wonder how much 20-30 japas x 108 times per japa recital must have=\r\n taken!&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;all&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If we look at tradition=\r\nal texts, the sandhya time starts two ghatikas, or two nadikas=A0before sun=\r\nrise, i.e. 48 minutes before sunrise, and it ends with the onset of sunrise=\r\n. So, in general, we can assume that about 48 minutes was spent in this par=\r\nti