long =\r\nas there are impurities in the mind and body, it is not possible to enter i=\r\nnto that realm easily. The gunas must be in a stable equilibrium. Neither t=\r\nhe laziness of Tamas, nor the impatience of rajas is conducive for it, but =\r\nthe stable, illuminating, self-assurance of satwa leading to a deeper equan=\r\nimity in mind and life is needed.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;Apparently, he also realized th=\r\nat there are some Tantrik mantras of Ma which serve a similar purpose as th=\r\ne Gayatri mantra. They take a person to the spiritual planes above.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;=\r\nSo I asked him why did you not continue the meditation or japa of Gayatri m=\r\nantra, since there was a nice experience. He said it would have pulled him =\r\nin and he\n would not have been able to continue the spiritual practices whi=\r\nch he was already doing for some time, and leaving something half way is no=\r\nt good.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Reading the explanation your provided below, that is : &lt;=\r\nbr&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&quot;We meditate upon that Savitaa (yaH) who impels (prachodayaa=\r\nt) our (naH) \nthoughts (dhiyaH). He blesses us with subtle eyesight. Withou=\r\nt his \nlight, we would not be able to distinguish different objects. This i=\r\ns \nexplained in the Aitaterya Upanishad=A0=93The sun, having become eyesigh=\r\nt, \nentered the eyes=94. He thus blesses all living beings.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;..=\r\n matches with the description that I had heard from my friend. Quite intere=\r\nsting!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Regards&lt;br&gt;=A0Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;=A0&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br=\r\n&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:1=\r\n6px&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;color:rgb(153,153,153)&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span =\r\nstyle=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman,new york,ti